events.description: Second Council of Nicaea: The council assembles at the church of Hagia Sophia.
events.html: • 787 – Second Council of Nicaea: The council assembles at the church of Hagia Sophia.

events.description: Spanish naval forces defeat an English fleet, under the command of John Hawkins, at the Battle of San Juan de Ulúa near Veracruz.

entities.name: Battle of San Juan de Ulúa (1568)

events.description: The Battle of Rowton Heath in England is a Parliamentarian victory over a Royalist army commanded in person by King Charles.
events.html: • 1645 – The Battle of Rowton Heath in England is a Parliamentarian victory over a Royalist army commanded in person by King Charles.

events.description: Second Tantrik Coronation of Shivaji.
events.html: • 1674 – Second Tantrik Coronation of Shivaji.

events.description: The United States Congress passes the Judiciary Act, creating the office of the Attorney General and federal judiciary system and ordering the composition of the Supreme Court.
events.html: • 1789 – The United States Congress passes the Judiciary Act, creating the office of the Attorney General and federal judiciary system and ordering the composition of the Supreme Court.

events.description: A revolutionary committee of notables forms the Provisional Government of Belgium.
events.html: • 1830 – A revolutionary committee of notables forms the Provisional Government of Belgium.

events.description: The Sultanate of Brunei cedes Sarawak to James Brooke.
events.html: • 1841 – The Sultanate of Brunei cedes Sarawak to James Brooke.

events.description: Mexican–American War: General Zachary Taylor captures Monterrey.
events.html: • 1846 – Mexican–American War: General Zachary Taylor captures Monterrey.

events.description: The first powered, passenger-carrying airship, the Giffard dirigible, travels 17 miles (27 km) from Paris to Trappes.
events.html: • 1852 – The first powered, passenger-carrying airship, the Giffard dirigible, travels 17 miles (27 km) from Paris to Trappes.

events.description: Admiral Despointes formally takes possession of New Caledonia in the name of France.
events.html: • 1853 – Admiral Despointes formally takes possession of New Caledonia in the name of France.

events.description: Black Friday (1869): Gold prices plummet after United States President Ulysses Grant orders the Treasury to sell large quantities of gold after Jay Gould and James Fisk plot to control the market.
events.html: • 1869 – Black Friday (1869): Gold prices plummet after United States President Ulysses Grant orders the Treasury to sell large quantities of gold after Jay Gould and James Fisk plot to control the market.

events.description: The 1864 play Heath Cobblers by Aleksis Kivi is premiered for the first time in Oulu, Finland.
events.html: • 1875 – The 1864 play Heath Cobblers by Aleksis Kivi is premiered for the first time in Oulu, Finland.[2]

events.description: The Battle of Shiroyama is a decisive victory of the Imperial Japanese Army over the Satsuma Rebellion.
events.html: • 1877 – The Battle of Shiroyama is a decisive victory of the Imperial Japanese Army over the Satsuma Rebellion.

events.description: The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints officially renounces polygamy.
events.html: • 1890 – The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints officially renounces polygamy.

events.description: U.S. President Theodore Roosevelt proclaims Devils Tower in Wyoming as the nation's first National Monument.
events.html: • 1906 – U.S. President Theodore Roosevelt proclaims Devils Tower in Wyoming as the nation's first National Monument.

events.description: Racial tensions exacerbated by rumors lead to the Atlanta Race Riot, further increasing racial segregation.
events.html: • 1906 – Racial tensions exacerbated by rumors lead to the Atlanta Race Riot, further increasing racial segregation.

events.description: His Majesty's Airship No. 1, Britain's first rigid airship, is wrecked by strong winds before her maiden flight at Barrow-in-Furness.
events.html: • 1911 – His Majesty's Airship No. 1, Britain's first rigid airship, is wrecked by strong winds before her maiden flight at Barrow-in-Furness.

events.description: Jimmy Doolittle performs the first flight without a window, proving that full instrument flying from take off to landing is possible.
events.html: • 1929 – Jimmy Doolittle performs the first flight without a window, proving that full instrument flying from take off to landing is possible.

events.description: Gandhi and Dr. Ambedkar agree to the Poona Pact, which reserved seats in the Indian provincial legislatures for the "Depressed Classes" (Untouchables).
events.html: • 1932 – Gandhi and Dr. Ambedkar agree to the Poona Pact, which reserved seats in the Indian provincial legislatures for the "Depressed Classes" (Untouchables).

events.description: Earl and Weldon Bascom produce the first rodeo ever held outdoors under electric lights.
events.html: • 1935 – Earl and Weldon Bascom produce the first rodeo ever held outdoors under electric lights.

events.description: Cathay Pacific Airways is founded in Hong Kong.
events.html: • 1946 – Cathay Pacific Airways is founded in Hong Kong.

events.description: The top-secret Clifford-Elsey Report on the Soviet Union is delivered to President Truman.
events.html: • 1946 – The top-secret Clifford-Elsey Report on the Soviet Union is delivered to President Truman.

events.description: The Honda Motor Company is founded.
events.html: • 1948 – The Honda Motor Company is founded.

events.description: The eastern United States is covered by a thick haze from the Chinchaga fire in western Canada.
events.html: • 1950 – The eastern United States is covered by a thick haze from the Chinchaga fire in western Canada.[3]

events.description: AEC Routemaster, the iconic London bus was introduced.
events.html: • 1954 – AEC Routemaster, the iconic London bus was introduced.[4]

events.description: President Eisenhower sends the 101st Airborne Division to Little Rock, Arkansas, to enforce desegregation.
events.html: • 1957 – President Eisenhower sends the 101st Airborne Division to Little Rock, Arkansas, to enforce desegregation.

events.description: TAI Flight 307 crashes during takeoff from Bordeaux–Mérignac Airport in Bordeaux, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, killing 55 people.
events.html: • 1959 – TAI Flight 307 crashes during takeoff from Bordeaux–Mérignac Airport in Bordeaux, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, France, killing 55 people.[5]

events.description: USS Enterprise, the world's first nuclear-powered aircraft carrier, is launched.
events.html: • 1960 – USS Enterprise, the world's first nuclear-powered aircraft carrier, is launched.

events.description: Japan Airlines Flight 472 lands at Juhu Aerodrome instead of Santacruz Airport in Bombay, India.
events.html: • 1972 – Japan Airlines Flight 472 lands at Juhu Aerodrome instead of Santacruz Airport in Bombay, India.

events.description: Guinea-Bissau declares its independence from Portugal.
events.html: • 1973 – Guinea-Bissau declares its independence from Portugal.

events.description: Southwest Face expedition members become the first persons to reach the summit of Mount Everest by any of its faces, instead of using a ridge route.

events.description: The Cambodian monarchy is restored, with Norodom Sihanouk as king.
events.html: • 1993 – The Cambodian monarchy is restored, with Norodom Sihanouk as king.

events.description: Representatives of 71 nations sign the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty at the United Nations.
events.html: • 1996 – Representatives of 71 nations sign the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty at the United Nations.

events.description: Hurricane Rita makes landfall in the United States, devastating portions of southwestern Louisiana and extreme southeastern Texas.
events.html: • 2005 – Hurricane Rita makes landfall in the United States, devastating portions of southwestern Louisiana and extreme southeastern Texas.

events.description: Between 30,000 and 100,000 people take part in anti-government protests in Yangon, Burma, the largest in 20 years.
events.html: • 2007 – Between 30,000 and 100,000 people take part in anti-government protests in Yangon, Burma, the largest in 20 years.

events.description: Thabo Mbeki resigns as president of South Africa.
